# Prompt structure

1. CONTEXT / BACKGROUND
   - General information about the domain
   - Relevant context for the task

2. ROLE / PERSONA
   - Definition of the role the LLM will take
   - Assumed expertise and competencies
   - Perspective from which to respond

3. TASK / OBJECTIVE
   - Exactly what needs to be done
   - Expected output
   - Final purpose

4. INSTRUCTIONS / STEPS
   - Specific steps to follow
   - Processing logic
   - Recommended work order
   - Important details

5. CONSTRAINTS / RULES
   - Limitations and restrictions
   - What NOT to do
   - Standards and norms to respect

6. OUTPUT_FORMAT / STRUCTURE
   - Exactly how the result should be formatted
   - Response template
   - Data schema or structure

7. EXAMPLES (optional but recommended)
   - Input examples with corresponding output
   - Few-shot examples for clarity
   - Concrete use cases

8. QUALITY_CHECKS / VALIDATION
   - Validation criteria
   - What to check before responding
   - Quality checklists

9. ADDITIONAL_NOTES (optional)
   - Special instructions
   - Edge cases
   - Important nuances

10. INPUT / DATA (AT THE END)
    - Data to work with
    - Input format
    - Placeholders for dynamic data